text: Aranzazu Gonzalez Muñoz (born June 5, 1975 in San Sebastian, Guipúzcoa) is a swimmer from Spain. She has a disability and is an S4 type swimmer. She raced at the 1996 Summer Paralympics in Atlanta, Georgia. She finished first in the 50 meter breaststroke, 50 meter freestyle and 100 meter freestyle races. == References == Category:Spanish swimmers Category:Living people Category:1975 births Category:Paralympic gold medalists for Spain Category:People from San Sebastian Category:1996 Summer Paralympics Category:Sportspeople with disabilities, type S4
